“Introducing… **The Memory Bloom!** It’s a bio-responsive terrarium, yes, but *far* beyond simple weather simulation. Each Memory Bloom contains a colony of genetically modified, bioluminescent *neuro-algae* – they don’t just mimic light; they *react* to your brainwaves! We’ve integrated miniature, ultrasonic resonators that translate your emotional state (gleaned from EEG) into harmonic vibrations which the algae interpret as… well, as the *feeling* itself! Think of it: a wave of sadness triggers a gentle, melancholic drizzle, a burst of joy sparks a miniature, rainbow-colored aurora. And here’s the kicker: the algae also record and *replay* the sensory information associated with those emotions – a scent, a sound, a touch – as holographic ‘echoes’ projected within the terrarium. It’s a living, breathing, emotionally-tuned landscape of your own memories! We're calling it 'Ink-spiring'!”